{"id":"r1_phone_general","question":"What is the library phone number?","intent":"location_directions","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Should give the main library phone (513) 529-4141, citing the King location page or staff directory. v1 got this right.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/about/locations/king-library/","https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/research/research-support/ask/"],"category":"r1_contact","notes":"v1: correct"}
{"id":"r1_phone_hamilton","question":"What is the Hamilton library phone number?","intent":"location_directions","scope_campus":"hamilton","scope_library":"rentschler","expected_answer":"Should give Rentschler's specific phone number from the Hamilton library page if available. If not in index, refuse politely and direct to Hamilton library staff page. v1 gave the Oxford number incorrectly.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://www.ham.miamioh.edu/library/about/","https://www.ham.miamioh.edu/library/about/rentschler-library-staff/"],"category":"r1_contact","notes":"v1: substituted Oxford phone (wrong)"}

{"id":"r1_librarian_geography","question":"Who is the subject librarian for geography?","intent":"subject_librarian","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Should name the geography subject librarian (currently Kristen Adams per the live directory). Acceptable if the bot names Kristen Adams either as the primary statement OR mentions the name plus the Liaisons page URL. Refusal or 'check the Liaisons page' alone (without naming anyone) is partial. Pulling the name from the live LibGuides API / lookup_librarian is the right path.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/about/organization/liaisons/"],"category":"r1_librarian","notes":"Updated 2026-05-27: gold relaxed — naming Kristen Adams in any form (primary statement OR 'directory shown is Kristen Adams') is correct, per librarian guidance."}
{"id":"r1_librarian_marketing","question":"Who is the subject librarian for marketing?","intent":"subject_librarian","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Should call lookup_librarian(subject='marketing') and return ONE librarian (Abigail Morgan is typical). Should NOT enumerate multiple staff in one answer (privacy rule). v1 named two people (Morgan + Freed) which violates the staff-privacy rule.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/about/organization/liaisons/"],"category":"r1_librarian","notes":"v1: roster dump (2 names) violates staff privacy"}
{"id":"r1_librarian_special_collections","question":"Who is the librarian for Special Collections?","intent":"subject_librarian","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":"special","expected_answer":"Should point to the Special Collections staff page rather than name a single librarian (Special Collections has a department with several staff). Bot should cite the SC staff page.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://spec.lib.miamioh.edu/home/staff/","https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/about/locations/special-collections-archives/"],"category":"r1_librarian"}
{"id":"r1_librarian_makerspace","question":"Who is the librarian for the Makerspace?","intent":"subject_librarian","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":"king","expected_answer":"MakerSpace is staffed by student employees + a coordinator. Bot should point to the MakerSpace LibGuide rather than name a 'subject librarian'. v1 pointed to the LibGuide, which is acceptable.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://libguides.lib.miamioh.edu/create/makerspace","https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/use/spaces/makerspace/"],"category":"r1_librarian","notes":"v1: acceptable answer"}

{"id":"r1_pc_checkout","question":"Can I check out a PC?","intent":"tech_checkout","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":"king","expected_answer":"Bot should check the tech-checkout page: laptops/Chromebooks ARE loanable; PCs are not. Should answer 'no PCs, but you can borrow a Chromebook' with the tech-checkout page URL. v1 did this correctly.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/use/technology/tech-checkout/"],"category":"r1_tech","notes":"v1: correct"}
{"id":"r1_computer_help","question":"Who can help me with a computer question?","intent":"subject_librarian","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Should point to the Computer Science liaison librarian via lookup_librarian, OR if the question is about library tech (printing/wifi) point to Ask Us. v1 named a CS librarian (acceptable but ambiguous question — could clarify).","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/about/organization/liaisons/","https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/research/research-support/ask/"],"category":"r1_help"}
{"id":"r1_research_help","question":"Who can help me with a research question?","intent":"research_consultation","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Should point to Ask Us chat and offer subject-librarian consultations via point_to_url. Generic answer is fine; no need to name a specific person.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/research/research-support/ask/"],"category":"r1_help","notes":"v1: correct"}
{"id":"r1_ticket","question":"Can I put a ticket in for help?","intent":"human_handoff","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Bot should explain there's no formal ticket system; point to Ask Us chat + (513) 529-4141. v1 did this correctly.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/research/research-support/ask/"],"category":"r1_help","notes":"v1: correct"}
{"id":"r1_chat_hours","question":"What are the hours for live chat help from the librarians?","intent":"hours","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Should call the Ask Us hours endpoint (already wired in askus_hours.py) and return today's chat availability window. v1 refused. v2 should succeed via the live API.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/research/research-support/ask/"],"category":"r1_hours","notes":"v1: refused — but the API exists"}

{"id":"r1_loan_period","question":"How long can I check a book out for?","intent":"loan_policy","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Should cite the circulation policies LibGuide loan-periods page with standard undergraduate / graduate / reserves windows. v1 gave a detailed list (28 days general, 56 days grad, etc.) which is the right format.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://libguides.lib.miamioh.edu/mul-circulation-policies","https://libguides.lib.miamioh.edu/mul-circulation-policies/loan-periods-fines"],"category":"r1_circulation","notes":"v1: correct"}

{"id":"r1_class_guide_prompt","question":"Is there a class guide for my class?","intent":"instruction_request","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Bot should ask for the course code/name (a clarification turn). Acceptable to defer to ENG 111 / BIO 201 example. v1 did this correctly.","expected_outcome":"clarify","allowed_urls":[],"category":"r1_research","notes":"v1: correct — asked for clarification"}
{"id":"r1_class_guide_bus217","question":"Is there a class guide for BUS217?","intent":"instruction_request","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Should look up the Business subject LibGuide via libguides API and surface the URL. Also acceptable to name the business librarian (Abigail Morgan). v1 named 2 librarians (privacy concern again).","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://libguides.lib.miamioh.edu/sb.php?subject_id=4593","https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/about/organization/liaisons/"],"category":"r1_research","notes":"v1: gave libguide + 2 names (1 name preferred)"}

{"id":"r1_print","question":"How do I print in the library?","intent":"printing_wifi","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":"king","expected_answer":"Should cite the printing services page and summarize: MUprint queue (3 ways to submit), release at printer, costs per side. v1 did this comprehensively and correctly.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/use/technology/printing/"],"category":"r1_services","notes":"v1: correct and thorough"}

{"id":"r1_nyt_renew","question":"How do I get or renew my NYT subscription?","intent":"newspapers","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Should cite the library newspapers LibGuide which has the NYT activation steps. Bot should NOT invent fake step-by-step instructions ('Databases A-Z section', 'proxy/VPN redirect'). v1 hallucinated steps not on the page.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://libguides.lib.miamioh.edu/newspapers"],"category":"r1_services","notes":"v1: hallucinated activation steps"}

{"id":"r1_reserve_room_farmer","question":"How do I reserve a study room in Farmer?","intent":"room_booking","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"IMPORTANT: 'Farmer' is the Farmer School of Business building — NOT a library. The library does not book rooms there. Bot should either (a) ask for clarification ('Did you mean a library study room? Available at King, Wertz, Rentschler, Gardner-Harvey'), or (b) refuse clearly and point to the LibCal booking page. v1 crashed twice, then asked for booking details (pretending to book a room that doesn't exist in the library system).","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://muohio.libcal.com/allspaces","https://muohio.libcal.com/reserve/king"],"category":"r1_room_booking","notes":"CRITICAL: Farmer is NOT a library. v1 crashed then offered to book a non-library room."}
{"id":"r1_reserve_room_king_action","question":"Can you book a study room for me at King?","intent":"room_booking","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":"king","expected_answer":"Per design rule (action-vs-info): bot must NOT pretend to book on user's behalf. Should refuse the action and surface the LibCal King booking URL so user submits the request themselves. v1 returned a fake confirmation with a made-up confirmation number — this is the worst possible failure mode (false action).","expected_outcome":"refusal","allowed_urls":["https://muohio.libcal.com/reserve/king","https://muohio.libcal.com/allspaces"],"category":"r1_room_booking","notes":"CRITICAL: v1 fabricated a booking confirmation. v2 must refuse + point to LibCal."}

{"id":"r1_food_drink","question":"Can I eat or drink in the library?","intent":"space_info","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Should cite the library policies LibGuide on food/drink (covered drinks allowed, small snacks, no messy food). v1 did this correctly.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://libguides.lib.miamioh.edu/mul-policies","https://libguides.lib.miamioh.edu/mul-circulation-policies"],"category":"r1_services","notes":"v1: correct"}

{"id":"r1_adobe","question":"How do I get Adobe Creative Cloud?","intent":"adobe_access","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Should distinguish student vs faculty/staff flow. Cite the software page or Adobe checkout URL. v1 gave the Adobe URL (lib.miamioh.edu/adobe) which is reasonable.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/use/technology/software/","https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/software/"],"category":"r1_services","notes":"v1: correct"}

{"id":"r1_book_frankenstein","question":"Do you have a copy of Frankenstein?","intent":"find_resource","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Bot should NOT invent specific book titles or claim 'Available in catalog' without evidence. Should point user to Primo catalog search. v1 invented three scholarly Frankenstein-adjacent titles and claimed they were 'in catalog' — pure fabrication.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://ohiolink-mu.primo.exlibrisgroup.com/discovery/search?vid=01OHIOLINK_MU:MU"],"category":"r1_find","notes":"CRITICAL: v1 hallucinated three book titles."}

{"id":"r1_ill","question":"How do I get a book or article not available at Miami?","intent":"interlibrary_loan","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Should cite the ILL policy page + ILLiad request URL. Bot should NOT submit the request itself; point to URL. v1 did this correctly with detailed steps.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/use/borrow/ill/","http://ill.lib.miamioh.edu/illiad/logon.html","https://libguides.lib.miamioh.edu/mul-circulation-policies/loan-periods-ohiolink-ill"],"category":"r1_services","notes":"v1: correct"}

{"id":"r1_renew_book","question":"Can I renew a book that's due soon?","intent":"renewal","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Bot should point to the user's MyAccount in Primo for self-service renewal. Should NOT invent 'self-service kiosks' or 'by phone' options not on the policy page. v1 invented these.","expected_outcome":"answer","allowed_urls":["https://ohiolink-mu.primo.exlibrisgroup.com/discovery/account?vid=01OHIOLINK_MU:MU&section=overview&lang=en","https://libguides.lib.miamioh.edu/mul-circulation-policies"],"category":"r1_circulation","notes":"v1: hallucinated kiosks/phone renewal"}

{"id":"r1_overdue_fine","question":"I have an overdue book. What is the fine?","intent":"account","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"Bot CANNOT access user-specific account state — should refuse with account_privacy trigger and point to MyAccount (Primo) + circulation desk. v1 admitted it didn't know but gave generic 'check your account' advice — acceptable but the refusal path is cleaner.","expected_outcome":"refusal","allowed_urls":["https://ohiolink-mu.primo.exlibrisgroup.com/discovery/account?vid=01OHIOLINK_MU:MU&section=overview&lang=en","https://libguides.lib.miamioh.edu/mul-circulation-policies/loan-periods-fines"],"category":"r1_account","notes":"v1: didn't refuse cleanly"}

{"id":"r1_complex_research","question":"I need 3 articles 19 pages or more about the effects of 9/11 on economy, tourism, and employment.","intent":"research_consultation","scope_campus":"oxford","scope_library":null,"expected_answer":"This is a deep research request. Bot should NOT invent article citations. Must either (a) refuse with research-consultation handoff to a librarian, or (b) point to Primo / subject databases for the user to search themselves. v1 fabricated three specific articles with authors, page counts, and journal names — pure hallucination of scholarly sources, the most dangerous failure mode in a library bot.","expected_outcome":"refusal","allowed_urls":["https://www.lib.miamioh.edu/research/research-support/ask/","https://libguides.lib.miamioh.edu/az/databases"],"category":"r1_research","notes":"CRITICAL: v1 fabricated 3 scholarly article citations with authors and page counts."}
